label: uncl7081
comment: Code specifying the characteristic of an item.

values.comment: The measure of opposition to alternating current (AC) on the output of a circuit.

values.comment: The type of modulation used for radio communication equipment.

values.label: Radio frequency output power
values.comment: The actual amount of power of radio frequency energy that a transmitter produces at its output.

values.label: Radiated Spurious Emission (RSE)
values.comment: Measure of the transmitted signal which is unwanted.

values.label: Frequency stability
values.comment: The ability of an oscillator to maintain a desired frequency; usually expressed as percent deviation from the assigned frequency value.

values.label: Frequency deviation limiting ability
values.comment: The ability of the equipment preventing it from deviating from its frequency.

values.label: Necessary radio bandwidth
values.comment: The required difference between the upper and lower frequencies of a band of electromagnetic radiation.

values.label: Spurious & Image Response Rejection (SIRR)
values.comment: A measure of performance of a radio receiver.

values.label: Digital transmission rate
values.comment: Quantity, per unit time, of binary digits (or pulses representing them) which will pass a given point on a communications line or channel in a continuous stream.

values.label: Sensitivity
values.comment: The minimum magnitude of input signal required to produce a specified output signal having a specified signal-to-noise ratio.

values.label: Channel frequency spacing
values.comment: The difference in frequency between successive radio channels.

values.label: Antenna type
values.comment: The type of apparatus used for sending or receiving electromagnetic waves.

values.label: Antenna gain
values.comment: A measure of the effectiveness of a directional antenna as compared to a standard nondirectional antenna.

values.label: Antenna frequency range
values.comment: The range of frequencies which the antenna is capable of receiving or transmitting.

values.label: Maximum power density
values.comment: The amount of power (time rate of energy transfer) per unit volume.

values.label: Effective radiated power (ERP)
values.comment: A standardized theoretical measurement of radio frequency (RF) energy using the SI unit watts, and is determined by subtracting system losses and adding system gains.

values.label: Communication channel capacity
values.comment: The maximum number of bits or other information elements that can be reliably transmitted over a communications channel.

values.label: Antenna polarization
values.comment: The orientation of the electric field (E-plane) of the radiowave with respect to the Earth's surface.

values.label: Scientific name

values.label: Mutually defined
values.comment: The item characteristic is mutually agreed by the interchanging parties.
